<title>USA: U.S. HEADLINE STOCKS -- Issues to watch - May 1.</title>
<headline>U.S. HEADLINE STOCKS -- Issues to watch - May 1.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1997-05-01</dateline>
<text>
<p>Stocks to watch this morning:</p>
<p>* Informix Corp reported a first quarter per share loss of $0.90 including charges compared with a profit ot $0.10 a year ago. The First Call estimate was for a loss of $0.30. The company said chief financial officer Alan Hendricks was resigning. It said it would take a second quarter charge for downsizing units with inadequate revenues.</p>
<p>The stock closed at 7-5/16.</p>
<p>* Mylan Laboratories Inc reported fourth quarter earnings of $0.11 per share compared with $0.15 a year ago. The First Call estimate was $0.13.  </p>
<p>Mylan closed at 12-3/8.</p>
